headline: Plane crash in Philadelphia neighborhood kills 7; several homes catch fire - CBS Philadelphia
summary: A medical jet crashed in Northeast Philadelphia, killing 7. The plane, carrying a Mexican patient and crew, caused fires and injured over 20. Authorities are investigating.

headline: Mother and child among seven killed in Philadelphia medical jet crash
summary: A medical transport plane crashed in Philadelphia, killing seven people, including a child and her mother. The jet was en route to Mexico and crashed minutes after takeoff, causing multiple fires. Investigations are ongoing.

headline: Philadelphia plane crash: 6 onboard during fiery crash near homes and mall
summary: An air ambulance carrying six people, including a pediatric patient and crew, crashed near a Philadelphia mall, resulting in fatalities and injuries. The cause is under investigation by the FAA and NTSB.
